result.name: Chan Kuen Kee Restaurant

reviews.text:
I came for an early dinner of udon noodles. The restaurant was not crowded and there were a few vacant tables.  The man in-charge at the cash-register speaks very good English and was very helpful.  

The large serving tasted right and had less salt which was good for me.  The veggies were crunchy and the pork was very lean. The udon was al dente.

They ran out of Coke Zero and Diet Coke, unfortunately.
Portions were big.  Food was good.  Reasonably priced.  Enjoyed alot!
Ok
General food and good for quick dinner after boat party.
